  "body": "As a user\nI want to see only the profile pictures of users I have added to my contacts\nSo that I won't be subject to inappropriate pictures in public chats\n\n\n### Description\n\nBecause of the demand for moderation in app stores to some apps, we decided to limit our exposure and protect users from inappropriate content.\nUsers should only be seeing profile pictures of other users if they added them as contacts.\n\n\n### Designs\n\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/TNCyHKtR3sx5EL6YznFWUa4O/Profile?node-id=4717%3A2107\n\n\n### Implementation\n\nThis will require a change in status-go to be feature-complete.\nIf we want to cut the scope to a minimum we can implement the design but grey out the other two options (`Everyone`, `None`), leaving `Contacts` as the only option, which does not require any status-go changes.\nUp to you, if de-scoped, please create a separate issue with the remaining work.",
